snippet.textDisplay: Possible mini theory: I was rewatching a let's play of five nights at freddy's 4 and it was the first scene with the crying child locked in his room. When selecting the toy versions of freddy, chica, bonnie and foxy the child stated that 'these are my friends'. Why would the crying child see them as his friends when he is terrified of the animatronics? Is it possible that this is the event he saw which made him so scared of the restaurant? The event being that his actual friends were murdered and stuffed into the suits and that's why the fredbear doll says 'don't you remember what you saw?' Just an idea

1983: No idea what's even going on??
1985: 5 murders but no possessed robots.
1987: No possessed robots except for foxy and mangle,possibly freed after the animatronics are dismantled. 5 More unpossessed murders.
1992:5 murdered kids possess the new animatronics,phone guy dies (Rest in peace,19XX-1992) Nothin' that major.
1992:Possibly sister location events,could be 1983 too.
1992?: Dave the aubergine man William Miller Afton gets impaled by sharp metallic spikes,but he always comes back.
2023?: Springtrap found and brought to Fazbear's Fright to die,Henry isn't able to get him this time.
FNaF 6: SL characters,the puppet and Afton are all defeated,Henry's insomnia is finally gone and REMEMBER,THAT'S JUST A THEORY,A GAME THEORY,Thanks for reading!
THE END! ❔

P.S. The puppet is also possessed during 1987,maybe (Probably) before then.
P.S. 2: I'll post this theory on the next video too (Or next FNaF video).

snippet.textDisplay: You've probably already thought of this and probably won't see this but the human eyes and teeth sort of remind me of how in I think it was fnaf 2 where phone guy said that after you got stuffed into a suit only your eyes and teeth would be visible to the other people on the outside. I think that the Plushtrap could be like that, and the chewing on the various doors in the house is the child trying to getaway. It could even fit in with the sister location animatronics since I think in the books they'd open up to snatch the children. My theory is the Plushtraps were sent out, sort of like a prototype, to test if the voice mimicking features work for child-snatching, and they did work but the only problem is they were too small, crushing any children inside the suit just like the old animatronics and pushing their eyes and teeth to the surface. Once the taking of the children was successful, the Plushtraps were programmed to go back to wherever they were produced so they could be assessed and, if necessary, remodelled which is again, is why it was chewing on the doors, trying to get out. It's probably wayyyyy off base since I haven't had a chance to read the new books yet and gonna get torn apart by anyone that sees it but its 'just a theory' based on what I've heard so far.

snippet.textDisplay: Hey matpat, what if psychic-friend fredbear is actually michael's (crying child's) brother's soul stuck in a plush. Maybe this was one of the reasons michael was crying all the time (he might have been there when it happened) and maybe thats why in fnaf 4 when you are walking around the town seeing all the other kids, the fredbear plush is always on screen, it could be because his older brother is trying to look out for him, on top of that, when he urges micheal to get out of the pizzeria it could be because he knows that thats where purple guy is murdering a bunch of kids and is afraid he would do the same to micheal. Heck maybe purple guy is the one who trapped his soul in the plush because he (the brother) found out about his murder habit and was going to report it. It could also explain why in fnaf 4 the brother (fake one) always scares micheal in a FOXY mask as its an animatronic from the pizzeria that all the murder happens so that micheal would become so scared if the animatronics there that he doesnt go there. Obviously this doesnt work as...well...the bite of 83 happens but it could be why the brother (fake) and his friends throw michael at the fredbear animatronic (to scare him even more) but hey thats just a theory, a GAME THEORY. Seriously though, please consider looking into it, thx.😀👍
